description:
Alarming Silence



Aired on 03/15/2010, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 16 August 1987, Northwest Airlines Flight 255, a McDonnell Douglas MD-82, stalls as it lifts off from Detroit Metropolitan Airport and crashes just beyond the runway, killing 154 of the 155 people on board; two people on the ground are also killed.
